<<BD_INVOKE>> 2025-11-30T13:26:38.409885042+00:00 "list"
<<BD_INVOKE>> 2025-11-30T13:26:55.599197699+00:00 "create" "--title" "Remove engine dependence on card text (use structured ability data)" "--priority" "1" "--description" "# Remove Engine Dependence on Card Text

## Problem

The Rust engine currently parses oracle text to determine card capabilities (mana production, keywords, etc.)
when this information is already available in structured form from the card files' ability notation.

Java Forge card files have explicit structured notation:
```
A:AB$ Mana | Cost$ T | Produced$ G | SpellDescription$ Add {G}.
```

The `Produced$` parameter explicitly declares mana production. We should NEVER need to grep card text.

## Current State

The Rust loader already parses `Produced$` correctly in `effect_converter.rs:150-185`:
```rust
ApiType::Mana => {
    let produced_str = params.get("Produced")?;
    // ...properly parses all cases
}
```

But `CardCache::new()` in `card.rs:158` ignores the parsed abilities and re-derives mana production
by grepping oracle text:
```rust
if text_lower.contains("{t}: add {w}") || text_lower.contains("add {w}") { ... }
```

## Goal

Move towards ZERO dependence on card text anywhere in the engine. All game-relevant information
should come from structured ability data parsed from card files.

## Occurrences to Fix

### 1. CardCache mana production (PRIORITY)
- Location: `mtg-engine/src/core/card.rs:158` - `compute_mana_production()`
- Issue: Greps text for "{t}: add {X}" patterns
- Fix: Derive from parsed `ActivatedAbility` with `is_mana_ability = true`

### 2. [TO BE POPULATED - search codebase]

## Implementation Plan

1. After abilities are parsed in card loading, derive `ManaProduction` from `ActivatedAbility` entries
2. Keep text-grepping as fallback ONLY for legacy/test cards without structured abilities
3. Eventually remove the text fallback entirely once all cards use structured data"
